The paper deals with a sampling theorem for functions defined on the three-dimensional rotation group, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), computer vision (cs.CV), scientific computing (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of fast algorithms to compute directional wavelet transforms on the sphere, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
